{
  "doc_id": "11583",
  "text": "Insulin and a number of other agents that activate protein synthesis (41) induce the rapid dephosphorylation of eEF2. This results in increased eEF2 activity and accelerated elongation [CITATION_1] . The dephosphorylation of eEF2 appears to be due to the inhibition of eEF2 kinase, which is also brought about by insulin. Both these effects are blocked by rapamycin [CITATION_2] .",
